abstract: >-
  A statistical platform for analyzing circadian clock-target gene dynamics 
  using AR(2) autoregressive modeling. The eigenvalue modulus |lambda| 
  quantifies temporal persistence in gene expression across 79 embedded 
  datasets spanning 5 species (mouse, human, baboon, Arabidopsis, yeast) 
  and ~125,000 unique genes. Features include: AR(2) eigenvalue profiling 
  with 6-check edge-case diagnostics, multi-tissue Phase Portrait Explorer 
  with BMAL1 coupling analysis (12 tissues, 636 gene-tissue tests), 
  root-space geometry with GO/KEGG enrichment, drug target overlay 
  (168 genes, 256 FDA drugs), literature validation against 59 curated 
  circadian genes, genome-wide coupling scan with BH-FDR correction, 
  ODE Model Zoo (5 models, 12/12 checks PASS), framework benchmarks 
  against ARIMA/OU/State-Space, 11-analysis robustness suite, and 
  custom CSV upload for real-time analysis.
